Phakaaathi has been led to believe that Mamelodi Sundowns are set to make announcements as far their personnel is concerned. WATCH: Mahlangu slams Sundowns for ‘destroying SA football’This website has it on good authority that Masandawana will not be renewing contracts of certain players, while some are set to go out on loan. Sundowns have got a few players whose deals are set to expire at the end of the season and the club has made it clear that they will not renew. Some of these players, as Mgosi Squad understands, are looking to sign pre-contracts elsewhere, while some want out immediately. “When there is a new guy in charge (Rulani Mokwena is fairly new as solo head coach) things are going to change because he wants to show his authority and make his own imprint on the team,” a source revealed.